MEDIA personality Pearl Thusi and content creator, Mr Smeg (Michael Bucwa), finally went on their big date. They went out for lunch on Saturday, 29 January and they broadcast it on YouTube. Their date topped the Twitter trends list, with people also taking part in the date via social media. The National Lunch Date, as it’s called, was held at Oskido’s restaurant, Daruma in Midrand and later moved to Konka in Soweto. They planned their date publicly on Twitter last week. This was started by when Pearl commented on Mr Smeg’s tweet about American singer, Ari Lennox. He said Ari wasn’t beautiful and Pearl Thusi commented and laughed at the tweet. She was then attacked by people on social media who said she was bad for laughing at a comment about the singer’s looks. ALSO READ : SAMAS EXTEND CLOSING DATE FOR ENTRIES! Their interaction led to them agreeing to go out together. As they days went, it went big as they also got sponsors to also be part of the lunch. Mercedes-Benz transported them to their date, they were dressed by Tshepo Jeans, Drip, Thabootys, Era By DJ Zinhle and more. Their date was filmed from the beginning and Mr Smeg brought the actress flowers and viewers noticed that he was a bit shy during their date, but the enjoyed watching it. They both thanked people who were part of the date. Pearl Tweeted: “Tell your friends to pull up is the strategy that will work. We will win if your friends PULL UP like @TshepoJeans @DJZinhle @casspernyovest @djsumbody @OskidoIBelieve @MichaelBucwa @Boity @Leratokganyago @LekauSehoana @Thando_Thabethe @LindaMoeketsi @KonkaSoweto @MercedesBenz” “We can all win if we just PULL UP!! It’s the little things that will create change,” she continued. “Thank you so much for all the Support,” tweeted Mr Smeg. She said they will planning another national date and asked people who they’d like to see. Tell your friends to pull up is the strategy that will work. We will win if your friends PULL UP like @TshepoJeans @DJZinhle @casspernyovest @djsumbody @OskidoIBelieve @MichaelBucwa @Boity @Leratokganyago @LekauSehoana @Thando_Thabethe @LindaMoeketsi @KonkaSoweto @MercedesBenz Thank you so much for all the Support ??   